---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pest Control Trinity Beach | Holiday Lets & Turnover"
  description="Pest control in Trinity Beach, Cairns — cockroaches, ants, mosquitoes, rodents and termites for the northern beaches and holiday-let turnover. Fast turnaround, recurring plans, free quote."
  canonical="https://cairnspestmanagement.com.au/trinity-beach/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Trinity Beach &middot; Kewarra Beach &middot; Clifton Beach &middot; northern beaches</span>
      <h1>Pest control in <span class="accent">Trinity Beach</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Trinity Beach is northern-beaches holiday country &mdash; a high proportion
        of holiday lets, Airbnbs and rentals turning over guests week to week. A
        cockroach, ant or mosquito problem in front of paying guests is a review
        killer, so turnaround matters. We handle cockroaches, ants, mosquitoes,
        rodents and termites, with fast and recurring options for property hosts.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Trinity Beach</span>
      <h2>Pest control built around guest turnover.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Holiday lets cannot afford a pest sighting.</h3>
        <p>
          A big share of Trinity Beach housing is <strong>holiday lets, Airbnbs and
          short-term rentals</strong>, and nothing tanks a booking rating faster
          than a guest spotting cockroaches in the kitchen or ants across the
          bench. Constant turnover, luggage coming and going, and bins cycling
          through mean pests get reintroduced regularly. We work to the changeover
          schedule and lean on a <strong>recurring plan</strong> so the property
          stays consistently clear between guests &mdash; see
          <a href="/services/general-pest-control/">general pest control</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Cockroaches, ants and mosquitoes by the water.</h3>
        <p>
          The beachside setting drives the three pests guests notice most.
          <strong>Cockroaches and ants</strong> thrive in the warm, humid coastal
          climate and around kitchens and outdoor entertaining areas, while
          <strong>mosquitoes</strong> breed in any standing water after the wet-
          season rains &mdash; pot saucers, blocked gutters, pool surrounds. We
          treat cockroaches and ants with gel baits and a residual barrier
          (<a href="/services/cockroach-ant-control/">cockroach &amp; ant
          control</a>) and can carry out mosquito harbourage treatment and
          source-reduction advice around outdoor living areas as part of a general
          treatment.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Rodents and termites near the coast.</h3>
        <p>
          The wet season brings rats and mice indoors here too, into roof voids and
          sub-floors &mdash; we bait safely and proof the entry points
          (<a href="/services/rodent-control/">rodent control</a>). And the coastal
          location does not spare termites: Coptotermes and Mastotermes stay active
          year-round, and salt-air-aged older beachside stock is exactly where they
          find a way in, so an annual <a href="/services/termite-control/">termite
          inspection</a> to AS&nbsp;3660 is well worth it.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Trinity Beach jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Fast changeover pest treatment on a holiday let between guests (~$215&ndash;$320)</li>
          <li>Recurring pest plan across an Airbnb or short-term rental portfolio</li>
          <li>Cockroach and ant treatment plus mosquito harbourage knock-down for an outdoor entertaining area</li>
          <li>Wet-season rodent baiting and roof-void proofing (~$180&ndash;$350)</li>
          <li>AS 3660 annual termite inspection on an older beachside home (~$235&ndash;$380)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/edmonton/">Edmonton</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/smithfield/">Smithfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/redlynch/">Redlynch</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/earlville/">Earlville</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cairns-region/">All Cairns Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Trinity Beach pest control quote.</h2>
        <p>Holiday-let specialists &mdash; cockroaches, ants, mosquitoes, rodents and termites. Fast turnaround, recurring plans.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
